OL,5,GThe BBC has announced that the
OL,6,Gtwice-nightly newspaper review on its
OL,7,GUK TV news channel will air for the
OL,8,Gfinal time on 2nd January 2023.
OL,10,FA press release issued a short time ago
OL,11,Fsaid the changes were part of plans to
OL,12,Fcreate a digital-first BBC.
OL,14,FDuring the summer, the BBC announced
OL,15,Fplans to merge the BBC News Channel
OL,16,Fwith its international equivalent. It's
OL,17,Fbelieved the merger will result in the
OL,18,Floss of 70 jobs, including 14 presenter
OL,19,Fposts.
OL,3,CBBC drops nightly newspaper review
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G1/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34302
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F343A1672708429
OL,5,FVarious media commentators have
OL,6,Fquestioned the BBC's ability to
OL,7,Fadequately cover UK breaking news on
OL,8,Fthe new TV news channel post-merger.
OL,10,FIn August, BBC News presenter Martine
OL,11,FCroxall warned about the potential
OL,12,Fimpacts of the channel merger in a
OL,13,Fseries of tweets. One of the tweets
OL,14,Fsuggested the paper review would be a
OL,15,Fcasualty. The tweets were deleted
OL,16,Fwithin hours.
OL,18,FThe statement issued by the BBC at
OL,19,F4.45pm today:
OL,3,CBBC drops nightly newspaper review
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G2/5
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
